00:12:01,880 --> 00:12:04,645
It was the unhappiest moment of mine,
all thanks to someone.

252
00:12:05,050 --> 00:12:07,959
First up, we have folk dancing.

253
00:12:07,960 --> 00:12:10,255
Please give a big round of applause
to your teachers.

254
00:12:10,890 --> 00:12:14,595
Let's start by standing an arm's width
away from everyone.

255
00:12:14,730 --> 00:12:17,799
We'll begin once you're ready
in your places.

256
00:12:17,800 --> 00:12:19,599
Hold both of your partner's hands,

257
00:12:19,600 --> 00:12:21,939
and ladies,
take a step with your right foot.

258
00:12:21,940 --> 00:12:23,069
Two.

259
00:12:23,070 --> 00:12:26,065
Turn around and clap twice.

260
00:12:26,240 --> 00:12:29,275
Then, get closer to your partner.

261
00:12:29,610 --> 00:12:32,079
I'll show you an example.

262
00:12:32,080 --> 00:12:34,975
So-hyun, I'm an amazing dancer.

263
00:12:51,900 --> 00:12:53,665
What are you doing? Put your foot out.

264
00:12:53,930 --> 00:12:55,665
What? Yes.

265
00:12:56,500 --> 00:12:58,565
I thought you told me that you got this.

266
00:12:59,170 --> 00:13:00,765
Right.

267
00:13:04,510 --> 00:13:05,605
Clap, clap.

268
00:13:10,280 --> 00:13:11,519
Should we go one more time?

269
00:13:11,520 --> 00:13:12,615
Sure.

270
00:13:14,090 --> 00:13:15,355
Hey!

271
00:13:15,420 --> 00:13:17,829
This folk dancing stuff is so annoying.

272
00:13:17,830 --> 00:13:20,955
Why are we dancing like pigs
all the way out here?

273
00:13:21,530 --> 00:13:23,395
- What do you mean?
- What?

274
00:13:23,660 --> 00:13:24,995
Pork dancing.

275
00:13:25,730 --> 00:13:26,925
Pig dancing.

276
00:13:29,500 --> 00:13:31,169
- Never mind.
- What's wrong with you?

277
00:13:31,170 --> 00:13:32,839
Hey, let's go over the steps.

278
00:13:32,840 --> 00:13:34,235
Look at those two!

279
00:13:36,340 --> 00:13:37,609
Could you please let my hand go?

280
00:13:37,610 --> 00:13:38,705
Yes.

281
00:13:39,110 --> 00:13:40,205
Sorry.

282
00:13:41,020 --> 00:13:42,115
Yes.

283
00:13:42,250 --> 00:13:44,785
Group Two, please get on stage.

284
00:13:46,690 --> 00:13:49,320
You guys have such an intense schedule.

285
00:13:48,420 --> 00:13:50,120
[ Seoyeon High Student Council
Meeting Schedule ]

286
00:13:49,590 --> 00:13:51,059
Can I take a look at it?

287
00:13:51,060 --> 00:13:52,155
Sure.

288
00:13:53,890 --> 00:13:55,899
I thought the broadcasting team had it
the most intense,

289
00:13:55,900 --> 00:13:57,455
but you guys are just as intense.

290
00:13:58,130 --> 00:14:00,925
Why are you in it? You seem like the type
who'd find this annoying.

291
00:14:01,370 --> 00:14:03,199
